'''Ding''' (also called ''Di'' or ''Dzing'') is a [[Bantu language]] that is spoken in the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]].
Maho (2009) considers the following to be distinct languages closely related to Ding: : B861 Ngul (Ngwi), B862 Lwel (Kelwer), B863 Mpiin (Pindi), B864 West Ngongo, B865 [[Nzadi language|Nzadi]] (See [[Boma–Dzing languages]].)
Only Ngul, which includes Ngwi,{{fix|text=is this the Ngwii dialect of Mbere?}} has an ISO code.
