'''Nzanyi''' (also known as Njanyi, Nzangi, Njai, Njeny, Zani, Zany, Jeng, Jenge, Njei, Njeing, Kobotshi) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in [[Nigeria]] in [[Adamawa State]] in the Maiha LGA, and along the border in [[Cameroon]].  Dialects are Dede, Hoode, Lovi, Magara, Maiha, Mutidi, Nggwoli, Paka, and Rogede.<ref name=e18/>

