{{Infobox person | name = Vasudeo Sitaram Bendrey | native_name = | image = Potrait_photograph_of_VS_Bendrey.png | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1894|2|13}} | birth_place = [[Pen, India]] | death_date = {{death date|1986|7|16}} | nationality = Indian | known_for = [[Indology]] }} [[File:Shivaji Maharaj by Von Valentyn.jpg|thumb|Portrait of Shivaji Maharaj found by Bendrey]] '''Vasudeo Sitaram Bendrey''' (13 February 1894 – 16 July 1986), popularly referred to as V.S.Bendre or V.C.Bendre in sources.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Lokrajya, volume 34|page=61|year=1978|quote=The recipients of awards included Ram Gosavi, the blind poet of Miraj in Sangli district and V. C. Bendre, the 84-year old historian.}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Gaekwad's Oriental Series, Issue 175|publisher=Oriental Institute|year=1995|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zFhOAQAAMAAJ&q=VC+bendre&dq=VC+bendre&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjVo5qsyPXZAhUKjFQKHQMuAMEQ6AEIMDAC|page=427|quote= “Banki Das ki Khyat ", ed. by Narottam Swami, Jaipur, 2013, V.S. Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj (Marathi), by V.C. Bendre, Poona...}}</ref> was a historian and author from the [[CKP]] community of [[Maharashtra]]. He won the Maharashtra state award for ''Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj Charitra''<ref>{{cite journal |title=The Illustrated Weekly of India |volume=91 |issue=3|page=8|date=July 1970 |publisher=Bennett, Coleman & Company |quote=(page 8)The Bakhar (diary) written by Anant Malhar Chitnis has proved valuable to historians including Grant Duff. There are renowned C.K.P. historians, too, like V. C. Bendre. His Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj Charitra has won the Maharashtra State Award.}}</ref> He is known for finding the true portrait of [[Shivaji]] (see inscription below portrait). He was a student of [[Vishwanath Kashinath Rajwade]] and worked for [[Bharat Itihas Sanshodhak Mandal]].{{citation needed|reason=portrait part is sourced by the image but not the Rajwade part and Mandal- although they are very likely true|date=March 2018}}
His works include "Sadhan-Chikitsa", which is considered a concise introduction to Maratha history and a guide for tools to conduct historical research.<ref>{{cite book |last=Bendrey|first=Vasudeo Sitaram |title=Sadhan-Chikitsa |publisher=Independent Publisher |date=2015 |isbn=9781467517874 |url= https://books.google.com/books/about/Sadhan_Chikitsa.html?id=IcsVRBS81_kC}}</ref> He wrote several books on the history of Marathas,<ref>{{WorldCat|id=lccn-n81072052}}</ref> and created indexes of [[Peshwa]]'s Daftar or historical records, known as "Bendrey's Indexes".<ref>{{cite book |last=Chitnis|first=KN |title=Research Methodology in History |publisher=Atlantic Publishers & Dist |date=1990 |isbn=9788171561216 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=azsdBX41x7oC&lpg=PA87&dq=v%20s%20bendrey&pg=PA87#v=onepage&q=v%20s%20bendrey&f=false}}</ref>
He brought to light how [[Sambhaji]] was misrepresented and proved that he had put up a strong resistance against foreign powers and made great contributions to the Maratha state.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lipare |first=Dayanand |date=23 April 2013 |title=इतिहासकार बेंद्रे यांची दुर्मिळ पुस्तके पुन्हा वाचकभेटीला |trans-title=Rare books of historian Bendrey are available|url=https://www.loksatta.com/maharashtra-news/rare-books-are-available-of-historian-bendre-103132/ |language=Marathi |work=Loksatta |location=Kolhapur |access-date=30 January 2018 }}</ref>
